This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with visual object recognition. The use of optical coherence and deep neural networks suggests that it may also fall under the optics (cs.OH) and information theory (cs.IT) categories. Additionally, the simulations and experiments performed may involve multimedia (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) aspects.
